 East London - The Buffalo City Metro on Monday again called on residents to take responsibility and heed the call to stay in their houses in order to help curb the spread of the Coronavirus (COVID-19). "Following numerous complaints about people roaming around in Mdantsane, members of the SANDF, SAPS and BCM Law Enforcement descended at the Mdantsane Mall today," the Metro said. "The fight against Corona virus is everybody’s business and people shouldn’t be policed in order to save their very own lives." Follow more RNEWS articles, subscribe to our YouTube channel and for breaking news LIKE us on Facebook. For news on the Western Cape click here. For great savings on life’s little pleasures visit Bargain Buys!  Know somebody who is getting married, Wedding and Function can assist.  Have kids, then you need to visit Kids Connection. Enjoy food and travel, then visit Home Food and Travel. Need assistance with an online presence, visit Agency One.  